  "prompt": "What does it feel like to hate a parent?",
  "response": "Feeling hatred towards a parent can be an intense and complex experience. Emotions might include anger, resentment, disappointment, or sadness. Sometimes, these feelings stem from unmet expectations, perceived neglect, or past trauma. It can also be accompanied by guilt or confusion, especially given societal and cultural expectations about familial bonds. It\u2019s important to explore these feelings through self-reflection or with the help of a professional therapist to understand their origins and work towards healing and reconciliation, if desired or possible.",
